    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter latest changes (I cannot yet point to a specific commit), requesting LSP hovering triggers a failure in the treesitter component which tries to call the `range` method, which is a `nil`.\n\nHere is a capture of the stacktrace.\n\n<img width=\"1611\" height=\"380\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a93555e9-46f6-4a5e-a39e-f0e63fb3f7db\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSend an `hover` request to the LSP client.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLSP hover window should display with treesitter highlighting.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2694+g 042c66e4f9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, does not have the feature\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux Ubuntu 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
