            "body": "Hmm, thank you, but that doesn't really narrow it down. (Except that you're using config for the obsolete `master` branch with the now-default `main` branch for nvim-treesitter -- plus some fields that were never part of the config! -- so some problems are to be expected.)\n\nBut nvim-treesitter (and mason!) should not be needed for this repro since the relevant parsers and queries are bundled with Nvim, so please try to cut the config down to just the LSP configuration (no treesitter), ideally with a basic `vim.lsp.config` call.",
