        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Well, the config doesn't specify the branch so you will get the default, which is main.\n> \n> But, yes, the legacy master branch is **not compatible** with Nvim 0.12 (since yesterday).\n\nGood to know, I'm still pinned to master with nvim-treesitter as well. I seem to get errors in markdown files\n\n```\n | Error: E5108: Lua: ...ike.smith/gitrepos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:196: attempt to call method 'range' (a nil value)\nstack traceback:\n\t...ike.smith/gitrepos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:196: in function 'get_range'\n\t...ike.smith/gitrepos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:231: in function 'get_node_text'\n\t...nvim-treesitter/lua/nvim-treesitter/query_predicates.lua:141: in function 'handler'\n\t...ith/gitrepos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:868: in function '_apply_directives'\n\t...ith/gitrepos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:1089: in function '(for generator)'\n\t...repos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:1123: in function '_get_injections'\n\t...repos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:690: in function '_parse'\n\t...repos/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:639: in function 'parse'\n\t...vim/lazy/vim-matchup/lua/treesitter-matchup/internal.lua:150: in function 'get_matches'\n\t...vim/lazy/vim-matchup/lua/treesitter-matchup/internal.lua:212: in function 'get_active_matches'\n\t...vim/lazy/vim-matchup/lua/treesitter-matchup/internal.lua:378: in function 'get_delim'\n\t[string \"luaeval()\"]:1: in main chunk\n```\n\nI pinned to `4ed597389c33fe22911d1d8bad93173ec24920cb` commit on Neovim and no longer have the issue.\n\nI tried upgrading to main on nvim-treesitter but noticed some inconsistencies with highlights so I rolled back to investigate when I have more time. \n\nJust commenting for information purposes incase this is helpful for others. Thanks!",
